is poetry and prose. Appointed official historian of Venice, after Morosina's death he became a cardinal. An open mind, coupled with staunch support of the established church during the troubled years of the reformation, made him an asset to the papal curia. At the time of his accidental death in Rome in 1547 he was considered a likely successor to Paul III.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 7aBIOGRAPHY & AUTOBIOGRAPHY / Religious.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978077357192140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780773571921423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780773571921/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles